properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, fourth Pacific survey flight, San Francisco to Guam and return; identified by donor with additional information: "Signed by entire crew, San Francisco - Honolulu, October 5-6; Honolulu - Midway, October 10; Midway - Wake, October 11 - 12; Wake-Guam, October 13."a. cover: green cachet at bottom left corner on front with illustration of aircraft in flight over globe with seahorse and text, "First flight eastbound from Guam, Pan American Clipper"; purple cachet at bottom right corner on front with illustration of aircraft in flight over route from San Francisco to Guam with text, "First flight westbound to Guam, Pan American Clipper"; three postmarks on front: October 5, 1935, San Francisco, October 16, 1935, Guam, and October 24, 1935, San Francisco with football-shaped killers over three stamps; two backstamps: October 5, 1935, Alameda, California, and October 13, 1935, Guam; signed by R.O.D. Sullivan, J. Tilton, M. [illegible], W. T. Jarboe Jr., H.R. Canaday, V.A. Wright.b. information sheet: 8 1/2 x 11 with black text; additional information prepared by donor, including route information; flight cover was received mounted to sheet with photo corners.
